In the JIRA rest api the following code does not let you create a component and provide the projectId: com.atlassian.jira.rest.v2.issue.ComponentResource#createComponent

Instead you need to provide the project key. Which seems like a bug. Especially because the rest api docs suggest that you should be able to provide the 'projectId' in the json blob: https://docs.atlassian.com/jira/REST/latest/#d2e5810

The task here is to make it so that the component create api can accept "project" or "projectId" for the creation of components. This would greatly help with the Atlassian Connect addon that I am writing.

